# Cursor Rules — Flyrank Frontend Internship Capstone

## Stack
- Plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript (no frameworks, no build tools)
- No package manager dependencies for now — vanilla front-end only
- Files opened directly in the browser for testing

## File structure
- index.html at the project root
- /css folder for stylesheets
- /js folder for JavaScript files
- /assets folder for images, icons, fonts, etc.

## Conventions
- Commit messages follow Conventional Commits format (feat:, fix:, docs:, chore:, style:, refactor:)
- Use semantic HTML elements (header, nav, main, section, footer) instead of generic <div> where possible
- CSS class names use kebab-case (e.g. .nav-bar, .hero-section)
- JavaScript variables and functions use camelCase
- Keep HTML, CSS, and JS in separate files — no inline styles or inline scripts
- Indent with 2 spaces
- Add comments for any non-obvious logic

## AI assistant guidance
- Prioritize clean, readable, beginner-friendly code over clever one-liners
- Explain any new concept briefly when introducing it
- Avoid adding frameworks or build tools unless explicitly asked

## Rules learned from AI workflow drill (FE-XX)
- Forms must include an explicit list of fields and validation rules in the prompt — 
  otherwise the AI adds unrequested fields (seen in round 1: 6 extra fields added 
  beyond what was asked)
- Always instruct the AI to check existing file contents before editing, to avoid 
  duplicate elements (e.g. duplicate <title> tags in <head>)
- Any form with validation must include: aria-invalid on invalid fields, 
  aria-describedby linking input to error text, and focus moved to the first 
  invalid field on submit — this must be explicitly requested and verified in 
  DevTools, not assumed